      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Each specimen dimensionally inspected via CMM prior to testing. Lot traceability documented. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 guidance. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading configurations, including at least two distinct offset distances or loading angles to characterize sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration (15 mm offset, axial compression-bending at 0° inclination). While the protocol is fully compliant with the standard, only one test condition was evaluated. Sensitivity of model predictions to offset distance and loading angle was not experimentally characterized. The achieved level of 2 falls short of the required level of 3 for this model risk level, as multi-condition coverage was not demonstrated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs match measured experimental conditions within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA model replicate experimental fixture geometry and loading points as measured. Grip compliance characterized experimentally and incorporated into boundary condition definitions. Input equivalency confirmed via pre-test simulation comparison. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy <10% relative difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance bounds.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: mean experimental 187.3 N/mm, FEA 191.1 N/mm (2.0% difference, E/uval=0.83). Yield force: mean experimental 412.6 N, FEA 404.8 N (1.9% difference, E/uval=0.71). Force at 40 mm: mean experimental 623.4 N, FEA 638.2 N (2.4% difference, E/uval=1.12). All QoIs within acceptance bounds. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
